  "texts": [
    "Conditional adversarial learning not only enhances the model's adversarial robustness but also indirectly increases the diversity of training samples.",
    "Assuming during the training process, the current episode (=i) employs adversarial learning, and perturbations are applied to all examples in the support set.",
    "In a subsequent episode (=j), if adversarial learning is not applied and, by chance, some examples are randomly selected from the support set of episode (=i).",
    "Consequently, the model is trained on the same samples with and without perturbations, thereby improving both the model's generalization and robustness.",
    "Additionally, selectively engaging in adversarial learning not only enhances model performance but also, compared to traditional adversarial learning, can save training time.In this paper, we conducted comparative experiments in Sect. 6.4 with different tasks and evaluation metrics, demonstrating the generalizability of our proposed conditional adversarial training for multiple tasks."
  ],
